title: For Sale:  WWI Model of 1917 Remington 12-18 30.06 Like British P17
location: I-30 and I-430, Little Rock, Arkansas
postcontent: Up for sale is a very nice December 1918 Remington WWI Model of 1917 rifle. The Model of 1917 was patterned after the British P17 and was actually the widest disseminated rifle and most widely used rifle by US soldiers in WWI. The Model of 1917 was built for the 30.06 round whereas the British P17 was .303. This rifle is of course 30.06 and all American made. The M1903 did not see nearly as much service in the war. This rifle has its original stock with several US ordnance flaming bombs on the receiver and bolt. It's reported that SGT Alvin York used the Model of 1917 when he capturd almost "the whole German Army" in WWI. He received the Medal of Honor for his gallantry. I will ship the rifle anywhere in the country to an FFL ($30) or anywhere in Arkansas for $25.

title: For Sale:  Remingon Model 700 ADL SA .243 WIN  (mfg. 1966)
postcontent:
I am selling my classic Remington Model 700 ADL short action chambered in .243 Winchester.  Beyond being an absolute tack driver, this particular rifle is a piece of American history.  It was manufactured in 1966 - the same year the USMC adopted the Model 700 as the M40 sniper rifle.  The accuracy of this rifle impressed the Marines; it will not disappoint you!

Like the original M40, this rifle is equipped with Weaver rings and a Redfield "Golden Five Star" 3-9x variable scope.   I purchased this rifle with the scope from the original owner.  I do not know if he was trying to duplicate the Marine rifle or if he simply purchased the best available on the market at the time.  The scope and the rifle are both old, but the years have not diminished their quality one bit.  It is an excellent optic on top of an excellent rifle.

Included in the sale is a slip-on LimbSaver recoil pad (the original metal buttplate gets punishing after a few rounds at the range), a Remington sling strap, a padded rifle case and about 150 rounds of .243 WIN ammunition - mostly 100gr. with 2 boxes of 80gr. too.

I am selling my classic Remington Model 700 ADL short action chambered in .243 Winchester. Beyond being an absolute tack driver, this particular rifle is a piece of American history. It was manufactured in 1966 - the same year the USMC adopted the Model 700 as the M40 sniper rifle. The accuracy of this rifle impressed the Marines; it will not disappoint you!

title: For Sale:  Gun Trust Services - Hanna Law P.C.
location: Serving all of Colorado, Denver, Colorado
postcontent:
Hanna Law, P.C. offers gun trust services to all of Colorado, and offers two levels of service: Basic Gun Trust for $225 and Comprehensive Gun Trust for $500

Are you looking to build an SBR? Maybe you're purchasing your first suppressor? A gun trust offers you a great deal of convenience when you own these items.

Hanna Law, P.C. is a different kind of law firm, specializing in firearms trusts. We do not operate on a normal business week schedule, but can accommodate your needs on your schedule. We are available during the day and in the evening as well as weekends.

We understand that buying an NFA item can be a lengthy process, so we strive to offer great service with a short turnaround.

We offer two levels of trust:
Basic Gun Trust $225 - fast and easy, convenient for those who do not wish to speak at great lengths with the attorney. If you e-mail your info and give us a call, everything can be handled in person very quickly. Notary services provided at time of delivery.

Comprehensive Gun Trust $500 - Also fast, however, the attorney will meet with you and discuss all the provisions of the trust. If you do not like specific provisions, need clarification on certain provisions, or would like to add or remove provisions, this is the level for you. Generally it takes 1.5-2 hours of face time with the attorney to go over the entire document. Notary services provided during meeting. This is a good option for those who are unfamiliar with firearms trusts, and demand extensive clarification. Some people are a bit nervous when starting their NFA item collection, and face-time with an informed attorney can put some of these concerns to rest.

For various reasons, you may wish to also put your Title I (regular) firearms into your trust as well. We also offer this service.

We wish you the best on your journey into the land of SBR's, AOW's, SBS's, and suppressors. They can be great home defense weapons, and sure are a whole lot of fun to shoot at the range. We hope to hear from you soon. Feel free to call at 720-568-0564. Leave us a voicemail with your number and a good time to return your call, and we will get back to you promptly. You can also e-mail us at info@hannalawpc.com.

title: For Sale:  Gun Trust Services - Hanna Law P.C.
location: Serving all of Colorado, Denver, Colorado
postcontent:
Hanna Law, P.C. offers gun trust services to all of Colorado, and offers two levels of service: Basic Gun Trust for $225 and Comprehensive Gun Trust for $500

Are you looking to build an SBR?  Maybe you're purchasing your first suppressor?  A gun trust offers you a great deal of convenience when you own these items.

Hanna Law, P.C. is a different kind of law firm, specializing in firearms trusts.  We do not operate on a normal business week schedule, but can accommodate your needs on your schedule.  We are available during the day and in the evening as well as weekends.

We understand that buying an NFA item can be a lengthy process, so we strive to offer great service with a short turnaround.

We offer two levels of trust:
Basic Gun Trust $225 - fast and easy, convenient for those who do not wish to speak at great lengths with the attorney.  If you e-mail your info and give us a call, everything can be handled in person very quickly.  Notary services provided at time of delivery.

Comprehensive Gun Trust $500 - Also fast, however, the attorney will meet with you and discuss all the provisions of the trust.  If you do not like specific provisions, need clarification on certain provisions, or would like to add or remove provisions, this is the level for you.  Generally it takes 1.5-2 hours of face time with the attorney to go over the entire document.  Notary services provided during meeting.  This is a good option for those who are unfamiliar with firearms trusts, and demand extensive clarification.  Some people are a bit nervous when starting their NFA item collection, and face-time with an informed attorney can put some of these concerns to rest.

For various reasons, you may wish to also put your Title I (regular) firearms into your trust as well.  We also offer this service.

We wish you the best on your journey into the land of SBR's, AOW's, SBS's, and suppressors.  They can be great home defense weapons, and sure are a whole lot of fun to shoot at the range.  We hope to hear from you soon.  Feel free to call at 720-568-0564.  Leave us a voicemail with your number and a good time to return your call, and we will get back to you promptly.  You can also e-mail us at info@hannalawpc.com.

title: For Sale:  Blast from the Past - Beretta Mod. 950BS Jetfire in .25 ACP.
postcontent: Beretta Mod. 950BS in .25 ACP. - Private sale of an older classic Beretta in very good condition. Made in Italy. When I called Beretta, they advised the gun's serial number predates their record keeping, and that based upon its features it had to have been manufactured sometime between 1950 and 1959. Bore is in excellent shape. I don't think it was shot much. Has a tip up barrel. Perfect gun for someone that is disabled, or has difficulty racking a slide (elderly, those with arthritis, small women etc...). You never rack the slide to shot this gun. You just drop a round in the tip up barrel, and once fired, it automatically cycles the next round. For a “mouse” gun, it has a large 8+1 capacity. Taurus also makes a small caliber tip barrel design, but has a much heavier trigger (due to being double action). The Beretta is only single action, (where the hammer resets due to the blowback from the fired cartridge, and not from pulling the trigger – The trigger only releases the hammer, which equals a light and smooth trigger). Very nice aged look. Nice, and small for concealed carry. Carry it with Hornady “magic” bullets, and it will be just as effective as a 40 caliber. I already have two (2) good shooting .25 acp caliber guns, and can't really justify keeping this one. Own a classic Beretta for only $165 (reduced). Private sale.
